As Senthuran wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/23/2004 at 13:14:41 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>If I have a lens with focal length f, back focal plane at -2f and 
>front focal plane at 2f...
>
>If I have two rays of light which are converging at -2f, will they 
>necessarily be converging at +2f?
>
>[Difficulty]
>
>
>[Thoughts]
>

Yes, assuming the thin-lens approximation.

The formula that relates d1 and d2 to f, where d1 and d2 are
the distances in front of and behind the lens of focal length f is:

1/d1 + 1/d2 = 1/f.

In your case, d1 = d2 = 2f, which works in the formula.


